Core Architecture

Questions load via:
fetch("questions.json")

Global state variables:
data
current
answers
flagged
timeLeft
timerInterval
isReady

Answer format:

answers[q.id] = { type: "mcq", value: 2 }
answers[q.id] = { type: "gridin", value: "12" }
Question Types Supported
Multiple Choice
type: "mcq"
choices: []
answerIndex

Example:

{
  "type": "mcq",
  "choices": ["A","B","C","D"],
  "answerIndex": 2
}
Grid-in
type: "gridin"
answer
answersAccepted
validation

Example:

{
  "type": "gridin",
  "answer": "11",
  "answersAccepted": ["11"],
  "validation": {
    "allowDecimal": true,
    "allowFraction": false,
    "allowNegative": true,
    "maxChars": 8
  }
}
Math Rendering

MathJax v3 is used.

Inline math:

\( ... \)

Display math:

$$ ... $$

Cancel package is enabled for expressions like:

\cancel{x}

Math is rendered via:

MathJax.typesetPromise()
Test Interface Features
Navigation

Buttons:

Prev
Flag
Next
Submit

Keyboard shortcuts:

A/B/C/D → select answer
ArrowLeft → previous question
ArrowRight → next question
Enter → next question
Progress Tracker

Top progress bar shows numbered pills.

States:

current
answered
flagged
unanswered

Flagged pills display a small flag icon badge.

Students can click pills to jump to questions.

Timer

Timer initialized from JSON:

"timeSeconds": 2100

Functions:

startTimer()
updateTimerDisplay()

When timer reaches zero:

submitTest()
Grid-in UX Improvements

Grid-in inputs now:

auto-focus when question loads

only focus if no answer entered

allow typing immediately

Calculator

Calculator implemented using embedded Desmos iframe.

Right-side drawer layout:

| Question Area | Calculator |

Calculator opens/closes with:

Calculator button

Embedded via iframe:

https://www.desmos.com/calculator

No API key required.

Stable Question Layout

Question and choices containers have fixed heights with internal scrolling:

#question
#choices

This prevents page jump when switching between long and short questions.

Scrollbar Styling

Thin modern scrollbars implemented for question and choices containers.

Skill Metadata

Questions contain hierarchical skill tagging:

skill:
  domain
  topic
  skill

Example:

"skill": {
  "domain": "Algebra",
  "topic": "Linear Functions",
  "skill": "Slope"
}
Post-Test Results Page

After submission:

Students see:

Score summary
Skill breakdown
Question review

Score banner displays:

correct
incorrect
unanswered
percentage
Skill Breakdown

Hierarchical structure:

Domain
  Topic
    Skill

Displayed in two-column layout.

Only skills that appear in the module are shown.

Students can click a skill to filter questions.

Review System

Review mode shows one question at a time.

Navigation:

Prev
Next
Back to Summary

Students must click:

Reveal Answer & Explanation

to see explanations.

Correct answers are highlighted in the answer choices.

The redundant text:

Correct answer: B

was removed to avoid duplication.

